---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lang = 'en';
const linkClass = 'text-paper transition-colors hover:text-amber-bright break-words';
const h2 = 'font-heading text-base font-semibold text-paper';
---

<Layout title="Privacy" lang={lang}>
  <div class="max-w-2xl">
    <p class="mb-4 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-amber">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tightish text-paper sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-9 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-fog">
      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>1. Controller</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">The controller within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is:</p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Adem Kocyigit<br />
          Tiefe Allee 33<br />
          24149 Kiel<br />
          Germany
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Email: <a href="mailto:0406adem@gmail.com" class={linkClass}>0406adem@gmail.com</a><br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+491732118910" class={linkClass}>+49 173 2118910</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>2. Hosting</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This website is hosted via <strong class="text-paper">Cloudflare Pages</strong> (Cloudflare, Inc.,
          101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). When the site is accessed, technically necessary
          connection data (e.g. IP address, user agent, date and time) is processed to deliver the content
          and ensure the security and stability of the service. The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
          (legitimate interest in a secure and stable provision of the website). Cloudflare may also process
          data in the USA; this is safeguarded by Standard Contractual Clauses and the EU-US Data Privacy
          Framework.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          Cloudflare privacy policy:
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={linkClass}>https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>3. Server log files</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When the website is accessed, the hosting provider automatically records technical data in log
          files, including the (shortened) IP address, date and time, browser type, referrer URL and amount
          of data transferred. This data is not merged with other data sources. The legal basis is
          Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>4. Email communication (Gmail / Google)</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Emails sent directly to me arrive in a Gmail mailbox provided by Google (Google Ireland Limited,
          Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland). On receipt and storage, technical connection and
          metadata is processed by Google. Google may also process data in the USA; this is safeguarded by
          Standard Contractual Clauses and the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you contact me by email, your details are processed for the purpose of handling your enquiry and
          any follow-up questions. I do not share this data without your consent. It is stored for as long as
          necessary to handle the request; statutory retention obligations remain unaffected. The legal basis
          is Art. 6(1)(b) and/or (f) GDPR.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          Google privacy policy:
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={linkClass}>https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>5. Cookies and tracking</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This website currently sets no tracking cookies of its own and uses no analytics tools. Should
          cookies or comparable technologies that are not strictly necessary be introduced in future, this
          will only happen with your explicit consent pursuant to § 25 (1) TDDDG in conjunction with
          Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>6. Fonts</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The fonts used (Inter and Clash Display) are hosted locally on the website's server (self-hosting).
          Loading the fonts transfers <strong class="text-paper">no data to third parties</strong> (such as
          Google Fonts).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>7. Embedded videos / media services</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Video work is only loaded after you actively click the respective preview image and is embedded via
          external players:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> Vimeo (Vimeo, Inc., 330 West 34th Street, New York, NY 10001, USA)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> Google Drive (Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Only on playback is data — including your IP address — transferred to the respective provider; this
          may involve a transfer to the USA, safeguarded by Standard Contractual Clauses and the EU-US Data
          Privacy Framework. The providers may set cookies in this context. <strong class="text-paper">No
          data is transferred to these services before you click.</strong> The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f)
          GDPR (legitimate interest in presenting my work samples).
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          Vimeo privacy: <a href="https://vimeo.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={linkClass}>https://vimeo.com/privacy</a><br />
          Google privacy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class={linkClass}>https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>8. Your rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">You have the right at any time to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> access to the personal data concerning you (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> rectification of inaccurate data (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> erasure of your data (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> objection to processing (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1 text-amber">—</span> lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">To exercise your rights, you can contact me at any time using the contact details above.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class={h2}>9. Status of this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">Last updated: June 2026</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
